<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f1031631999593>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Focus summoned or real?</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Sep 10th 12:41 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=63784><span id= >flatsnap</span></a><br><span id=notbold>45 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.86]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Good post, I just have a few things to add.<br><br>1. Shoulders increase the duration of all your buffs. This is a must for mana conservation. you will have to cast all your buffs on yourself, your pet, and your group less often. It will also save you reagents for the same reason. I no longer use this as I have a roykl's channeling crystal with the same effect which allowed me to get a much nicer shoulder item.<br><br>2. The levels of the focus Items are similar to the items with &quot;effect I, II, III&quot; as in each one is required to effect spells of a higher level. The higher level summoned focus items do indeed work on all spells below them. I hadnt heard about the stats not working but that would make sense.<br><br>3. I have only used the earing once and found that I did not need to give up 5 int to this piece as I became quite adept at managing aggro without it having primarily solo'd most of my career.<br><br>4. The necklace is another thing that I would just rather spend the plat on components then use mana to cast it or bother switching it on and off while buffing. There are far better neck pieces to wear then the summoned one.<br><br>5. I didnt wear the ring ONE day and I will always have one on when we decide to go kill some sketchy mob. I was summoned by Nezekhazena after she gated and I had time to attempt gating twice before I was mush between her toes. Had I been wearing the ring, there is a good chance I would have gotten gate off without being interupted, or had a third attempt. You have been warned, there is no better item in a dire emergency. I really miss those 3 blues of exp.<br><br>6. I havent mentioned the bracer because you are insane not to use it. It adds a maximum of 20 percent on the top end of your nukes. Enough said. (scars of sigil: 450 dd maxing at 540. 540-450=90, 90/450=.20 if you want to see the math yourself)<br><br>7. I am 55 and have the final line of focus items. One good way to make a little extra cash on the side is to Auc that you are summoning focus items for donations. Wizards especially are addicted to these and most often I get between 40 and 60 P to summon a ring and a bracer for them. If someone is interested but has never tried them, give them a set for free and you will have a customer for life. <br><br>Hope I have been helpful and not to long winded<br><br>Volcanus Eruptus<br>55 DE Mage<br>Vallon Zek<br><br>Someday I will PK someone from Defiant<br>/shakes his fist</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
