	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93315><span id=Scholar>Jeroo</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>51 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Here's the rundown on the effects and percentages of summoned focus items:<br><br>1. Earring - reduces mana usage by 15% for &quot;damaging&quot; spells. i.e. malosini, nukes, etc.<br><br>2. Shawl - increases durations of buffs that you cast by 15%<br><br>3. Ring - reduces casting time of spells that you cast by 20%.&nbsp;&nbsp;The exceptions are spells under 2.0 seconds and &gt;9.5 seconds, which it doesn't effect at all.<br><br>4. Bracelet - increases nuke damage by 20%<br><br>5. Necklace - gives a 15% chance of not using a reagent when casting a spell.<br><br>Note that NO FOCUS ITEM REDUCES AGRO!  This is a MISTAKE by castersrealm that they have refused to fix, even in the face of dozens of emails from myself and other mages.  Other sites just pass on the bad information.</p>&nbsp;<br>--<br>Jeroo Ashstaff</td></tr>
